# Deferred work

- Buildout: janus (forward-auth on edge, currently parked), hubble (monitoring
  on services), gaia + soyuz + hermes (Home Assistant, Zigbee, MQTT)
- The https://x homepage (landing page on the edge) needs the atlas
  intermediate re-issued with the name constraint widened to also permit the
  bare `x` label
- Verify Traefik actually renews the short-lived (24h) atlas certs in time
  before relying on it; bump the leaf duration if it's too lazy
- harmony -> backend hops cross the physical trunk since the edge tier split:
  AdGuard's UI (polaris.x -> :3000) travels plaintext — give backends atlas
  certs (re-encrypt end to end) or explicitly accept the exposure
- Populate the untrusted VLAN (60): the VLAN exists on vanguard but has no
  forward rules yet — add internet-only egress, no inter-VLAN access;
  intra-VLAN isolation via Proxmox per-VM firewall (and switch port isolation
  on nexus)

- NTP redirect rule: force IoT devices with hardcoded public NTP (pool.ntp.org)
  to use vanguard instead (outbound UDP 123 redirect)
- Tighten firewall forward rule 310 (services -> iot) to gaia's address once
  gaia exists (Zigbee coordinator hop: SLZB serial socket is TCP 6638)
- Once polaris serves encrypted DNS, switch firewall forward rule 215
  (trusted -> polaris) from plaintext 53 to the TLS port (853 DoT / 443 DoH)
  and drop plaintext
- Lock down pioneer (label printer) to only the protocols it actually needs:
  restrict trusted -> pioneer to its print ports (e.g. IPP 631, raw 9100) and
  drop everything else, once the device is on the network and its real port
  usage is confirmed
- mDNS repeater between services and iot if a device needs auto-discovery
- Remove default-log from the input chain once the network is stable (keep it
  on forward)
- Configure eth1 (5G backup WAN) and WAN failover
- Ship vanguard logs to hubble via remote syslog (Grafana + Loki + Alloy) and
  add the management -> services syslog firewall rule
- Consider restricting the forward ICMPv6 rule to specific types (currently
  allows ping between all VLANs)
- Replace the Proxmox API self-signed cert with an atlas-issued one and drop
  `insecure = true` from terraform/providers.tf once atlas exists
- Scope the Terraform Proxmox token to a dedicated terraform@pve user with a
  minimal custom role (privsep 1 + ACLs) instead of the root@pam privsep-0 token
- Docker Compose service hygiene: audit every existing role so each service
  meets the "Service definition hygiene" requirement in CLAUDE.md.
- Retire the shared `genesis` docker network: with DNS-01 no service needs the
  ACME hairpin anymore, and the Docker unity role (its last user) is gone —
  only the `docker network create genesis` task in the docker role remains.
  Drop it once comfortable nothing else relies on it.
- Tighten firewall forward rule 710 (edge -> services): currently unscoped like
  rule 310. Scope to the actual backend ports (atlas 9000, atlas-ca 9001,
  AdGuard UI 3000, knot DDNS 5354, DNS 53) once the backend set stabilizes.

- Commission the SLZB Zigbee coordinator for the gaia/soyuz buildout: space
  name, static address on the iot VLAN, and pick the Zigbee channel against
  the Wi-Fi plan (Wi-Fi is on 2.4 ch 6; Zigbee 25/26 dodge it but sit near
  the neighbors' ch 11, Zigbee 15 collides with ch 6).

- Update the bad gateway error page served by harmony (Traefik) to match the
  homelab's visual style instead of the default Traefik error page.

- Audit container logs across all VMs (`docker logs <name>`) for silent errors
  and warnings; fix or suppress anything that shouldn't be there.
